Part 1: 
1. My proposed Row Key for the EV dataset would be to use the VIN, Postal Code, and Model. 
This avoids hotspotting because a VIN is unqiue and it is a randomly assigned number. 
This means that the row keys get spread out evenly across all the Bigtable servers, and data
won't pile up in one place. Cars from the same city and even year will be on different servers
because the VINs are different. The effect on searching by city with this row key would be 
inefficient. City isn't included in the key I chose, and Bigtable isn't able to query rows for 
certain cities. Due to this, every row would have to be checked. Similarily, searching by make
would also be inefficeint because it isn't included in the key. Model exists in the key, but that
is at the very edn so without knowing the VIN or postal code, Bigtable won't be able to query cars
by make or model. 

